First, total sum of all numbers:  
11 + 13 + 14 + 16 + 16 + 18 =  
(11+13)=24, (24+14)=38, (38+16)=54, (54+16)=70, (70+18)=88  
So total = 88. We need 57, so we need to exclude numbers summing to 88 − 57 = 31.

So equivalently: find a subset to exclude (sum = 31), then the rest sum to 57.
